Notes: Taxonomy: Alfalfa, grown as a cover crop, is terminated in its first year, and so is never really established.
Notes: Environmental Tolerances: put "requires heat" as a comments notes; not tolerant of low K soil conditions.
Notes: Growth, Roots, and Nutrients: For successful alfalfa establishment the soil should be firm (packed). A small seed, it should not be planted too deep, only up to Â¼ inch deep. Most establishment problems have resulted from planting the seed to deep. In mixes, include this in the small box of the drill or adjust the drill accordingly that the seed is not placed too deep.     Floweing Time: The onset of floral development is controlled primarily by temperature and photoperiod. In midsummer, flower buds may appear on alfalfa regrowth three weeks earlier than in the spring when temperatures are lower and the photoperiod shorter.
Notes: Disease & Non-Weed Pests: Non host for sugarbeet cyst nematode and a poor host for soybean cyst nematode. Host for root knot nematode and Penetrans Root-Lesion Nematode.
Notes: Excellent grazing and forage harvest value but slow to establish, so may not be ideal for annual row crop systems.
